                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d601">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Griscom</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-07-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 20, 1903</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Griscom reports, in continuation of his telegram of July 14, that he is
                    credibly informed Japan will propose to Russia: <list>
                        <item>First. Integrity of China, and Chinese sovereignty in Manchuria to be
                            maintained.</item>
                        <item>Second. Russia not to administer Manchuria nor keep troops therein
                            except necessary guards near railroads.</item>
                        <item>Third. Japan to recognize all Russian rights in Manchuria based on
                            treaties and conventions now published.</item>
                        <item>Fourth. Russia to recognize that Japan is interested in a peculiar
                            degree politically as well as commercially and industrially in Korea, as
                            already stated in Anglo-Japanese treaty alliance.)</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
